issue.title: Meraki Sensors Timeseries
issue.body:
Hi,
I have a problem with meraki sensors.
In fact, when their telemetries are sent back to the gateway, timestamps are not kept because they are provided as defined in RFC3339 (aka. 2023-10-23T15:00:00Z).
I therefore lose the history of these metrics.
Other types of timestamp format should be taken into account.

comment.body: Indeed, I agree with you to add a user parameter to take into account the date format coming from the sensor

comment.body:
Hi @lsenecaux,

Thanks for your interest in ThingsBoard IoT gateway. We understand your idea, added in this PR. But it covers only one corner case, in this case we should have some generic solution for all converters to allow users provide their date formats and give ability to dynamically configure that. 

Please add changes to make it generic, you can use "dateFormat" parameter in converter configuration, for example.
Or we can add it in one of next releases as a separated feature.
